===Etymology===
Late Latin '''hypocorisma''', a loan from Greek noun υποκορισμα ('''hypokorisma''') from the verb υποκοριζεσθαι ('''hypokorizesthai''' = 'to call by pet names'). The Greek verb ''hypokorizesthai'' is compounded from [[υπο]] ([[hypo-]] = 'under, beneath, secretly') + κοριζεσθαι (korizesthai = 'to [[caress]]'). In the verb you can see the word κόρος (koros = '[[boy]]') or κόρη (korè = '[[girl]]').

